<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="574" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,615,2028]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1931,1956]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is High Valyrian, a fictional language created by George R. R. Martin in his novel “A Song of Ice and Fire”. Dracarys means “dragon’s fire” and it is a command used by Daenerys Targaryen to make their dragon’s breathe fire. The name represents the color pattern on the wings of this new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
