<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="576" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1863,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1935,1960]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Comments.</emphasis>
Despite the external similarity of 
<taxonomicName authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[719,854,1935,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dracarys" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[719,854,1935,1960]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">D. dracarys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[860,924,1935,1960]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[860,924,1935,1960]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
to 
<taxonomicName authority="Siewert, Madruga, Mielke &amp; Dolibaina" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="electrinus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[960,1105,1935,1960]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">D. electrinus</emphasis>
Siewert, Madruga, Mielke &amp; Dolibaina
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[269,333,1969,1994]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[269,333,1969,1994]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1942" box="[348,499,1969,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heraclides">
<emphasis box="[348,499,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">D. heraclides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[555,744,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mabille &amp; Boullet" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[555,740,1969,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenicoides">D. phoenicoides</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the general pattern of its male genitalia resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hewitson, 1877)" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1877" baseAuthorityName="Hewitson" baseAuthorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helixus">
<emphasis box="[1322,1435,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">D. helixus</emphasis>
(Hewitson, 1877)
</taxonomicName>
, especially at the distal margin of the aedeagus, with a straight and narrow spine-like process, and
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,210]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
the vesica with a needle-like cornuti (
<bibRefCitation box="[596,857,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" refId="ref4060" refString="Burns, J. M. &amp; Janzen, D. H. (2000) Drephalys: division of this showy Neotropical genus, plus a new species and the immatures and food plants of two species from Costa Rican dry forest (Hesperiidae: Pyrginae). Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 53, 77 - 89." type="journal article">Burns &amp; Janzen 2000</bibRefCitation>
). However, the above-mentioned valva characters distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[281,415,185,210]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dracarys" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[281,415,185,210]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. dracarys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[421,485,185,210]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[421,485,185,210]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
from its congeners.
</paragraph>
